From: pocknix
Subject: [PATCH] mangoapp: pace redraws to gamescope frame messages (stop free-running)

WHY (measured on the RP6, docs/gamescope-fps-investigation.md "GPU-side session"):
mangoapp's main loop has NO pacing for the visible-overlay case. `new_frame` is set by
the msgrcv thread when gamescope sends a frametime message, but it is NEVER cleared —
after the first message it latches true forever and the loop becomes a free-running
render loop, throttled only by glfwSwapBuffers. Every swap damages the overlay layer,
which forces gamescope to run its (expensive, rotated) composite; every composite lets
the next swap through. Result on the RP6: mangoapp GPU submits in 1:1 lockstep with
gamescope composites at 72-120/s against a ~44fps game — the composite tax measured at
up to ~32-41% of the GPU, costing ~10 fps with the Steam performance overlay on.

Upstream deliberately replaced the old `mangoapp_cv.wait()` with nothing/usleep because
a blocking wait while HIDDEN hangs keybind detection (their comment retained below).
This patch keeps that concern addressed while fixing the visible case:
 - consume `new_frame` after rendering (redraw only once per gamescope frame message,
   i.e. once per game/base-plane frame);
 - only run the hide-the-window branch when the overlay is actually disabled
   (`no_display`) — previously "visible but no new frame yet" could hide the window;
 - otherwise block on the condition variable WITH A 100ms TIMEOUT, so keybinds are
   still polled and the hidden case cannot hang (strictly better than the old
   usleep(500000): 10Hz instead of 2Hz keybind polling).

--- a/src/app/main.cpp
+++ b/src/app/main.cpp
@@ -12,6 +12,8 @@
 #include <stdio.h>
 #include <thread>
 #include <unistd.h>
+#include <chrono>
+#include <condition_variable>
 #include "../overlay.h"
 #include "notify.h"
 #include "mangoapp.h"
@@ -423,7 +425,13 @@
             ImGui_ImplOpenGL3_RenderDrawData(ImGui::GetDrawData());

             glfwSwapBuffers(window);
-        } else if (!mangoapp_paused) {
+            // Consume the frame token: one redraw per gamescope frame message.
+            // (Previously new_frame was never cleared -> free-running render loop.)
+            {
+                std::unique_lock<std::mutex> lk(mangoapp_m);
+                new_frame = false;
+            }
+        } else if (real_params->no_display && !mangoapp_paused) {
             glClearColor(0, 0, 0, 0);
             glClear(GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT);
             glfwSwapBuffers(window);
@@ -446,7 +454,10 @@
             // std::unique_lock<std::mutex> lk(mangoapp_m);
             // mangoapp_cv.wait(lk, []{return !get_params()->no_display;});
         } else {
-            usleep(500000);
+            // Wait for the next frame message; timeout keeps keybinds responsive
+            // and avoids the hidden-case hang the comment above describes.
+            std::unique_lock<std::mutex> lk(mangoapp_m);
+            mangoapp_cv.wait_for(lk, std::chrono::milliseconds(100), []{ return new_frame; });
         }
     }

